A performance of mounted archery or <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yabusame" target="_blank"><em>Yabusame</em></a>, as part of Kyoto’s famous <a href="https://www.japan-guide.com/e/e3948.html" target="_blank">Aoi Matsuri</a>. An archer  - with a traditional bow and in period costume - rides his horse at a full gallop while shooting three arrows at different targets. In the photo above, you can see the archer’s arrow shatter the wooden target into multiple pieces.
</p>
<p class="jp">
京都の有名な「<a href="https://souda-kyoto.jp/event/detail/aoimatsuri.html" target="blank">葵祭</a>」の一環として行われる<a href="https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%B5%81%E9%8F%91%E9%A6%AC" target="_blank">流鏑馬</a>。伝統的な弓を持ち、時代衣装を身にまとった射手が、馬を疾走させながら3本の矢をさまざまな的に放ちます。上の写真では、射手の矢が木製の的を複数の破片に砕くのが見えます。
</p>

